mcneill calls american indians and africans little more than the victims of the west in this book . he explains that they have little role in the development of culture ( which he sees as passing from society to society from mesopotamia on , like some sort of conceptual olympic torch ) and some get it and others do not . it is an outdated and bigoted way to see cultural history , and difficult to read without cringing . that said , the book contains marvelous elements . few writers will explain with his brevity and mastery how cultures have passed elements , one to another , over the expanse of time ; few writers can convey the forward momentum of history as mcneil . so with all its faults , it is very worthy book , certainly worth reading while keeping in minds its somewhat dramatic shortcomings
