there are many books on arm 's architecture or manual references . so far , this book is the only book which concentrates on the firmware development side . both assembly language and c are discussed , which is a relief for embedded/firmware engineers like me who like to combine both languages in a project . the 15 chapters in the book are : 1- arm embedded systems 2- arm processor fundamentals 3- introduction to the arm instruction set 4- introduction to the thumb instruction set 5- efficient c programming 6- writing and optimizing arm assembly code 7- optimized primitives 8- digital signal processing 9- exception and interrupt handling 10- firmware 11- embedded operating systems 12- cache 13- memory protection units 14- memory management units 15- the future of the architecture the strength of this book lies on the extensive examples on how to program arm effectively . it is a nice guide for those who want to learn arm programming style
